Rating: 4
Easy, quick recipe. Made as directed. I thought the flour might make the soup too thick, but it was perfect. I did puree about 1/2 of the potatoes which made for a creamy broth. Wonderful for a cold evening by the fire. I will definitely add this to my collection of winter soups.

Rating: 4
I'm not one to change the recipes before I try them, but I took the previous reviewers' advice and omitted the flour. I used extra Yukon Gold potatoes and sharp cheddar instead of gruyere, and I blended the entire pot of soup with a hand held blender, leaving plenty of potato still cubed. Really worked out very nicely. Good hearty soup.

Rating: 3
This is an easy, quick recipe, ideal for a winter lunch, and a good 'template' for other potato soups. Made with sharp cheddar instead of gruyere and a hefty splash of dark beer, this is standard stick-to-your ribs pub fare. I did omit the flour as I'm not partial to the glutinous texture that would have been contributed by so much flour, and finished the soup with just a dab of heavy cream, which I found smoothed the 'edges' and rounded out the flavors nicely.

Rating: 4
I have made this soup many times, and it is one of my favorites. I use yukon gold potatoes and I puree all of the soup with my hand blender. The gruyere cheese complements the other flavors in the soup well.

