This was an easy and fantastic recipe. I didn't read the reviews prior to making this soup, but I also used about a cup and a half of leeks, primarily because I was low on onions. Also, I cooked the bacon separate and used the food processor to chop. I added the bacon at the end with a little cream to ade a velvety texture. My taste tester (mom) thought it was the greatest. This will become a New England winter special in my house.

